Welcome to the Global Coffee analysis!




About

Objective

With these visualizations we would like to shed light on quality, quantity, and equity factors across different regions for the benefit of coffee producers, enthusiasts, investors, and policymakers. Through analysis and visualizations of the dimensions of coffee production and consumption, including import-export dynamics, coffee prices, and overall coffee aspects and quality. For example, we were particularly interested in further exploring the differences between countries that primarily export coffee versus those that import it. It became apparent that we all think it’s important to have a better understanding of where commodities like coffee come from and how it actually gets to our mug every morning.

ICO Dataset

The ICO Dataset, or International Coffee Organization Dataset, is a comprehensive compilation of coffee statistics worldwide. It encompasses data from various sources, providing insights into coffee consumption, production, exports, prices, and more. With 12 files and 336 columns, this dataset covers a wide range of aspects related to the coffee industry, spanning from 1990 to the present day. From disappearance and domestic consumption to exports, prices, and production, the ICO Dataset offers valuable information for researchers, industry professionals, and enthusiasts alike.

Coffee Quality Dataset

The Coffee Quality database from the Coffee Quality Institute (CQI) provides in-depth reviews of Arabica and Robusta coffees, covering aroma, flavor, acidity, and more. The dataset also comes with metadata on processing methods and origins, such as, country of origin, region, altitude, and farm name. This datasource is sourced directly from the Coffee Quality Institute.

Harvested Bags Per Year

×

Harvest Bags Per Year

Delve into the dynamics of coffee production over time with our Harvested Bags per Year Dashboard. Utilizing data from the ICO Coffee Dataset, this dashboard allows you to explore harvest yields across different years. Simply double-tap on a year to input a specific harvest year, or toggle between years using the provided arrows. Hover over any country to see the recorded number of bags harvested in that year, providing valuable insights into the dataset's coverage and the global coffee industry's dynamics. Please note that while these numbers represent a portion of total coffee production, they offer significant insights into production trends.

Taste Profile

×

Taste Profile

Explore the intricate flavors of coffee from around the world with our Taste Profile Dashboard. This dashboard provides insights into coffee flavor profiles sourced from the ICO Dataset. The ICO Dataset offers scores for each bag of coffee across categories like Aroma, Balance, Body, Flavor, and Sweetness, rated on a scale from 0 to 10. Use the user-friendly sliders or input specific ranges to filter the data and observe the number of bags falling within your selected parameters. Discover the origins of these coffees and gain new insights into average scores per country as you hover over each location.




Business

An Overview of the Coffee Business

Consumption

×

Consumption

Explore top-producing countries’ domestic consumption stats measured in KG per capita per year. Hover over the squares to see total production and other stats. To see how these countries are distributed on the global map, scroll down to the second visualization.

Production

×

Production

Explore countries’ total coffee production measured in millions of KG of coffee produced per year. Countries are ordered by their geographical area and colored by their total production amount. Hover for more information about each country and coffee production stats.

Import/Export

×

Import/Export

This viz shows the geographical distributions of top-exporting, top-importing, and top-re-exporting countries. The size and color of bubbles represents the quantity of these measures, in units of millions of KG of coffee. Exports refer to the amount of coffee exported from a country, imports refer to the amount of coffee imported into a country, and re-exports refer to the amount of coffee re-exported after being imported into a country.

Countries that Both Produce and Consume Coffee

World

×

World

In this visualization, the top plot is comparing the production vs consumption of each continent. The units of measure in the top chart are in units per one million people. To get an understanding of how much each continent is producing and consumer per capita (times one million) hover over the each globe that shows the corresponding continent you wish to view. At the bottom of the page, you can toggle the through the years. The bottom chart is showing the overall production and consumption each continent. Hover over the bars to see how much each continent is producing and consuming in total. To view other years, toggle the years below.
